{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Psa|12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","chapter":12,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:12:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":12,"verse":1,"text":"Help, Lord, for no faithful one remains; the loyal have disappeared from the human race.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:12:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":12,"verse":2,"text":"They lie to one another; they speak with flattering lips and deceptive hearts.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:12:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":12,"verse":3,"text":"May the Lord cut off all flattering lips and the tongue that speaks boastfully.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:12:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":12,"verse":4,"text":"They say, “Through our tongues we have power; our lips are our own —who can be our master?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:12:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":12,"verse":5,"text":"“Because of the devastation of the needy and the groaning of the poor, I will now rise up,” says the Lord. “I will provide safety for the one who longs for it.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:12:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":12,"verse":6,"text":"The words of the Lord are pure words, like silver refined in an earthen furnace, purified seven times.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:12:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":12,"verse":7,"text":"You, Lord, will guard us; you will protect